The path ~/.pythonhist is used by bpython but not CPython.

## Ubuntu Resolute Racoon (26.04 LTS)

Python 3.14.4
- has ~/.python_history
- does not have ~/.pythonhist

## macOS Tahoe (26)

Python 3.9.6 with readline
- has ~/.python_history
- does not have ~/.pythonhist

## Windows 11

Python 3.14.3 vanilla 64-bit
- has %userprofile%\.python_history
- does not have ~/.pythonhist

Python 3.12 vcpkg 32-bit
- does not keep history after the console is closed.
-->
<cleaner id="python">
  <label>Python</label>
  <option id="history">
    <label>History</label>
    <description>Delete the command history</description>
    <action command="delete" search="file" path="~/.python_history"/>
    <action command="delete" search="file" path="~/.pythonhist"/>
  </option>
</cleaner>
